So basically I just wanted to say fuck you to those counselors. Kids with disabilities can achieve great things regardless of statics and opinions. (8/8)

I just wanted to share this because the way I was treated in high-school really keep me from achieving my full potential and damaged self confidence because I was told I wouldnt succeed because of my mental health disorder. (7/?)

I felt that if I could achieve that goal then I would finally prove to myself that all those things they said were wrong and at the end of my first semester I achieved my goal of a 4.0 GPA something I was told was impossible for me to achieve. (6/?)

At the beginning of 2021 I decided to go back to school to get second degree this time in business with a certification in marketing, I set a goal that I would get a 4.0 GPA because I had never been able to achieve that before. (5/?)

I graduated with honors with my first degree an AA in graphic design in 2017. I had a 3.5 GPA so I just barely qualified for honors but I was super proud that I had done it when all I heard for four years from my high-school counselors that I would fail (4/?)

It wasn't until I got into college that I realized just how much I had put myself down because of their words and school became so much easier when I wasn't constantly watched and put down for my grades and my mental health disorder. (3/?)

Granted I had good grades in high-school but I didn't achieve in every class and they would constantly focus on my bad grades which I maybe had one or two in courses I wasn't good in, but I tried really hard. They made me feel like I was extremely stupid because this. (2/?)
